  "texts": [
    "(12), each outcome panel characterizes a distinct trajectory with specific structural properties.",
    "First, both trajectories originate from a common baseline: the pretreatment observations ⃗ Y 0.",
    "Beginning in round t = 1, these trajectories diverge into two distinct outcome vectors ⃗ Y 1 (w 1) and ⃗ Y 1 (w ′ 1).",
    "Crucially, while these outcomes differ, their distributions emerge from ⃗ Y 0 according to the same mathematical rule (the ESE mapping f 1 (•)) applied to different inputs w 1 and w ′ 1, respectively.",
    "This parallel evolutionary mechanism persists throughout the experiment timeline, generating two distinct but structurally parallel potential evolutions (Figure 4)."
